The article discusses the opposition towards Gina Haspel, the acting director of the CIA, by some senators. It argues that these senators are prioritizing their political interests over national security. It highlights that policymakers who approved and were briefed on enhanced interrogation techniques are the ones responsible for the program, not officers like Haspel who served honorably. The article also mentions that Haspel has been repeatedly vindicated in regards to allegations that she ordered the destruction of interrogation tapes. It states that the charges against her are false and inaccurate. The article concludes by emphasizing that current and former intelligence officials have praised Haspel for her honesty, commitment to the rule of law, professionalism, and high moral character.